# MIDAS debugging (`debug.mdc`)

Applies when the agent needs to debug, diagnose, or inspect a MIDAS component. Read/inspect only; does not authorise shared-environment mutations (see `.cursor/rules/jenkins.mdc`).

## Core principle

MIDAS lives inside the private VPC. The laptop cannot reach EKS, RDS, ElastiCache, or internal ALBs directly. All diagnostic commands run **on the jumpbox** via SSM.

| Key | Value |
|---|---|
| Region | `us-east-1` |
| VPC | `vpc-0c4d673f3e95a93eb` (EV-vpc) |
| Jumpbox EC2 ID | `i-04231b2a8a4d98b63` |

Source of truth: `.cursor/rules/solution_const.mdc`.

## Rule 1: debug EKS from the jumpbox via SSM

The jumpbox has an EKS access entry with cluster-admin scope (see `deploy/ecs-app/eks-jumpbox-access.tf`). Run `kubectl` on the jumpbox, not on the laptop.

### One-shot command

```bash
aws ssm send-command \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --instance-ids i-04231b2a8a4d98b63 \
  --document-name "AWS-RunShellScript" \
  --comment "MIDAS debug: <reason>" \
  --parameters 'commands=["kubectl <subcommand> <args>"]'
```

Retrieve output:

```bash
aws ssm get-command-invocation \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --instance-id i-04231b2a8a4d98b63 \
  --command-id <id>
```

### Interactive session

```bash
aws ssm start-session --target i-04231b2a8a4d98b63 --region us-east-1
# then run kubectl inside the session
```

### Rules

- Always pin `--region us-east-1` and `--instance-ids i-04231b2a8a4d98b63`.
- Default to read-only `kubectl`: `get`, `describe`, `logs`, `top`, `events`.
- Any mutating verb (`apply`, `delete`, `rollout restart`, `scale`, `edit`) requires explicit user approval and is an exception to pipeline-first (`.cursor/rules/jenkins.mdc`).
- Never port-forward the EKS API to the laptop. Never add a public endpoint for debugging.
- Do not copy kubeconfig, credentials, or tokens off the jumpbox.
- If `kubectl` context is missing, refresh on the jumpbox: `aws eks update-kubeconfig --region us-east-1 --name <cluster-name>`. Discover the cluster name with `aws eks list-clusters`; do not hardcode it.

